pesto puff pastry sticks - I always serve these together with soups, stews, tapas or appetizers - you can make them with all kinds of pesto, purée, olives, fresh vegetables, herbs or spices. I’ve reposted the recipe below - I hope the video explains the steps, but let me know if you have any more questions! 🥖

//ingredients:
1 sheet puff pastry
3 tablespoons green pesto
100g. shredded cheese / vegan cheese
salt & pepper
2 tablespoons of plant butter, melted 
sesame seeds
follow the video steps and bake until crispy for 10-12 mins at 200ºC (390ºF) 🤍

25 min lasagna soup 🍝 this is one of my favorite dinner recipe - you get all the good flavors of a delicious hearty lasagna in a comforting soup form. It’s loaded with vegetables, lentils, tomatoes and Italian herbs. I’ve shared the ingredients below

// ingredients:
3 cloves of garlic
1 onion
2 teaspoons of paprika
1 teaspoon of dried basil
1 teaspoon of cumin
200g chopped mushrooms 
2 carrots
1 can of lentils, cooked (240g)
2 cans of chopped tomatoes
3 cups of vegetable broth
3-4 lasagna noodles/pasta (broken into pieces)
salt and pepper 
oil for frying 
parmesan (I used a vegan version) 
- cook until the pasta is al dente. ask if you have any questions 🍂🤍

christmas cinnamon bread ❄️ no december without this homemade vegan cinnamon bread aka babka bread! I make this recipe every year in dec, sometimes with blueberry marmalade/compote, chocolate or cinnamon. I’ve reposted the recipe below, perfect to make for the upcoming weekend! 

//dough ingredients: 
1,5 dl. of oatmilk or almond milk
20g. fresh yeast
1/2 tablespoon of cardamom
50g. sugar
1/2 teaspoon of salt
300g. flour
40g. plant butter, soft

//method:  mix all the dough ingrediens in a mixer (except flour and plant butter). Mix well at low speed until combined. add the flour slowly. Chop the butter and add small pieces while mixing until the dough is completely smooth, elastic and shiny. let the dough rest for 1 hour.

//cinnamon filling:
50g. plant butter, soft
1 tablespoon of cinnamon
50g. sugar

//method:  mix all the cinnamon ingredients together. If the filling is too wet, let it rest in the refrigerator for 10 mins until you get a spreadable consistency.
Roll out the dough into a rectangle on a lightly floured surface. Spread the cinnamon filling an even layer on top of the dough. Use both hands to roll up the rectangle like a roulade, starting from the long side closest to you and ending at the other long end. divide the log into two long even halves, with the layers of dough and filling visible along the length of both halves. Lift the dough on top of each other, repeat to create a simple two-pronged plait. Transfer into a bread pan covered with baking papir. Bake for 15-20 mins at 180°C (350°F) hot air. Cool down and decorate with icing sugar on top.

30 min. taco soup - warm, spicy, healthy and easy-to-make soup with chili, kidney beans, vegetables, coriander and crispy tortilla chips. reposted this recipe so you can save this for later! 🏷 

//ingredients:
4 cloves of garlic
1 onion
2 teaspoons of paprika, sweet
2-3 teaspoons of chili
2 teaspoons of coriander
2 red pepper, 150g.
100g. mushrooms
1/2 eggplant
2 cans of tomatoes
400g. chili beans (1 can), drained 
500 ml. vegetable broth

//method:  finely chop garlic & onions. Cook in a big skillet, add the spices and cook for a few minutes. Add the finely chopped mushrooms, red bell pepper and eggplant - cook 5 more mins until tender. drain the chili beans, add into the soup + 2 cans of tomatoes. add the vegetable broth and cook for at least 10 minutes. add more liquid if it’s too thick. taste and add seasonings and more chilli if needed. serve the soup with black pepper, crispy tortilla chips, coriander and avocado.

25 min. homemade winter pumpkin pasta 🌨 this recipe can be made with any kind of winter pumpkins, store bought pumpkin purée & types of pasta (vegan and gluten-free). I’ve reposted the recipe below, so you can save this for later! 🍝 let me know if you have any questions. 

//pumpkin purée:
1/3 hokkaido pumpkin / 400g.
1 tablespoon of plant milk
1 tablespoon of plant butter
salt & pepper 
cook the pumpkin in 15 mins until soft and tender. add into a blender and mix with milk, butter, salt and pepper.

//pasta ingredients:
400g. pasta of choice, cooked al dente 
1-2 tablespoons of olive oil for frying
1 onion, finely chopped
2 cloves of garlic, finely chopped
2 teaspoons of paprika, sweet
1-2 teaspoons of chilli (can be omitted) 
1 teaspoon of cumin
1 tablespoon of tomato paste (for thickness) 
1 cup of plant milk 
parmesan cheese, dairy free
for serving: salt, pepper and fresh thyme 

let me know if you have any questions making it! 🍝

30 min. healthy january salad idea - with baked beetroot, carrots & chickpeas, cooked quinoa, spinach, oranges & blueberries. Made this last weekend and I’ve eaten it everyday since. Easy to storage in a airtight container the full week for an easy dinner or lunch. ✌🏼🍊

//ingredients; 
1/2 cup of quinoa, cooked
250g. beetroot
200g. carrots 
fresh thyme
100g. chickpeas, cooked
2 teaspoons of paprika + chilli 
a handful of spinach 
1/2 cup of cucumber, chopped
2 oranges, sliced
fresh blueberries
50g. feta cheese, I used plant based feta 
salt and pepper

Cook the quinoa according to package instructions. Meanwhile, add the chopped beetroot, carrots and chickpeas on a tray. Add fresh thyme, 2 teaspoons of paprika, salt, pepper and 1 tablespoon of olive oil. Mix it all together and bake at 200ºC (390ºF) for 20 mins until soft and crispy. 

In a big bowl add the fresh spinach, cooked quinoa, baked vegetables, chickpeas, cucumber, slices of oranges, fresh blueberries, feta cheese - top with salt and pepper before serving.

25 min. ONE POT quinoa soup 🥘 healthy dinner idea packed with vegetables, proteins and spices - you can add any leftover vegetables to this one and adjust the white butter beans with other legumes. Save this easy-to-follow dinner recipe for later on // recipe below 🫶🫶

//ingredients; 
1 onion
2 gloves of garlic
4 carrots, medium size
3 celery
1 tablespoon of ginger, shredded
2 teaspoons of paprika
1 teaspoon of rosemary
1 teaspoon of chilli flakes 
1 liter of vegetable broth
250 ml. tomato (canned tomatoes or passata)
100g. quinoa seeds, white
1 can of cooked butterbeans or white beans, 400g.
A handful of fresh kale

In one pot, cook finely chopped onions, garlic, carrots celery and ginger. Add the spices and cook for a few minutes. Add 1 liter of vegetable broth, canned tomatoes and raw quinoa. Cook for 10 minutes until the quinoa is cooked. Stir while cooking. 
Add the precooked butterbeans and a handful of fresh green kale. 

For servering; sprinkle with parmesan (I used a dairy-free version), sea salt & black pepper. Enjoy! 

-

20 min green lunch idea. These protein-rich panini toasts is a meat free version made with extra firm tofu, green pesto and spinach - but this basic recipe is easily changed up with vegetables, spices, herbs or melted cheese (I use to make these for easy lunch or dinner). PS this recipe is vegan and can easily be gluten-free too! recipe below 🫶 

//ingredients; 
200g. tofu (extra firm tofu)
a handful of spinach
1 red onion
1 avocado
1 teaspoon of garlic powder (or 1 clove of garlic) 
1-2 teaspoons of mustard, dijon
1 teaspoons of chili flakes 
juice from 1/2 lemon
2 tablespoons of green pesto 
salt and pepper 
4 slices of toast bread, glutenfree if needed

In a big bowl add mashed tofu (extra from), add finely chopped spinach, red onions, mashed avocado, garlic powder, mustard, chili flakes, lemon juice, green pesto - sprinkle with salt and pepper. Top with other bread slice. 
Heat a toaster in medium-high heat; spray lightly with cooking spray. Place the tofu sandwich and close the toaster. on the pan; toast until crispy and grill marks appear, 3 to 5 minutes.

here is my favourite miso soup recipe🍜 If you’re not already a miso lover, this recipe will convert you! It’s the easiest 20 min soup with mushrooms, kale, tofu, spring onions and cilantro. Full of miso taste, spicy pepper, protein & vegetables. 

//ingredients (serves 2); 
200g. tofu, extra firm
200g. mushrooms
1 liter of water
2 tablespoons of miso paste, brown
spring onions
a handful of green kale
2 carrots 
fresh cilantro
black pepper

Heat 1 liter of water in a pot, add the miso paste and mix well in the cooked water. In the soup; add finely chopped spring onions, brown mushrooms, extra firm tofu cubes and cook for a few minutes. 
Add the fresh kale and serve in bowls + topped with sliced carrots and fresh cilantro. Taste with black pepper and add more spiceness if needed.

Jeg har testet måltidskasserne de sidste 3 uger, og må bare sige, at det er nemme og super lækre opskrifter + at man undgår madspild og sparer meget tid og indkøb! Hver uge er der 18 forskellige retter at vælge imellem - og min kode gælder til alle deres måltidskasser, uanset om du vil afprøve den grønne vegetariske (ligesom jeg), den familievenlige, kalorielette eller mange flere. Jeg er blevet ret glad for deres vegetarkasse, da jeg også oplever, at opskrifterne er veganske i stort set alle tilfælde med fokus på grøntsager og proteiner - og så kan man altid nemt selv tilføje eget tilbehør oveni! 🌿

The best and crispiest potato rösti fritters 🥔🏷️ made with danish organic potatoes, zucchini and carrots - ready in no time and super easy to make!

here is what you’ll need:
250g. potatoes, organic - shredded
100g. zucchini, organic - shredded
100g. carrots, organic - shredded
2 tablespoons of flaxseeds + 2 tablespoons of water
3 tablespoons of corn starch
3 tablespoons of flour, gluten-free if needed
2 teaspoon of sweet paprika
salt and pepper

mix all ingredients in a big bowl, set aside in the fridge for 10 minutes before forming info fritters / rösti. You can cook these fritters with some oil on a pan or use an air fryer for an even result! I’ve tested both, and the result is sooo good! 🫶
